# AGENTS.md

Portable kernel for **any** coding agent. Keep short. Depth loads on demand (skills / RPI / graph).

**Product:** skysthelimit · **Tasks:** Linear `SKY-XX` · **Stack:** [`.agents/STACK.md`](.agents/STACK.md)

---

## Commands

```bash
npm install && npm run dev
npm run lint          # types + react version
npm test
npm run build
npm run graph:query -- "<task>"
npm run goal -- status
npm run goal:verify   # lint + test (done criteria)
npm run ship:eval     # deterministic ship graders
```

---

## Behavior (Karpathy)

1. **Think before coding** — state assumptions; ask if unclear; surface tradeoffs; push back on bad plans.
2. **Simplicity first** — minimum code that solves the ask; no speculative abstractions or unrequested flexibility.
3. **Surgical changes** — touch only what the task requires; match local style; mention unrelated smells, don’t “fix” them.
4. **Goal-driven execution** — define verifiable success; loop until `npm run goal:verify` (or task-specific checks) passes.

---

## Ship loop (RPI — HumanLayer / YC-style)

For non-trivial work, **do not one-shot**. Use phases (artifacts under `.agents/goals/<slug>/`):

| Phase | Output | Stop when |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| **R** Research | `research.md` — files, flows, risks (graph:query first) | You can name exact files to touch |
| **P** Plan | `plan.md` — steps + **verify check per step** | Human/agent agrees criteria |
| **I** Implement | code + tests | `npm run goal:verify` green |

```bash
npm run goal -- start "short title"     # creates goal dir + GOAL.md
npm run goal -- phase research|plan|implement
npm run goal:verify
npm run goal -- done                    # only after verify passes
```

Skill: `.agents/skills/ship-loop/SKILL.md` · Workflow: `.agents/workflows/ship-loop.md`

---

## Project style

- Next.js App Router · TypeScript under `src/`
- Industrial UI: **radius 0** · `#FF5A00` on charcoal · **no emojis** in product source
- Root cause only (no soft-skip “fixes”) · public claims must be verifiable

---

## Context rules

| Load always | Load on demand | Never bulk-load |
|-------------|----------------|-----------------|
| This file | Skills (`SKILL.md`), one at a time | `graphify-out/wiki/**`, `GRAPH_REPORT.md` |
| | `.agents/STACK.md`, domain prompts | Full skill packs, hub dumps, ontology novels |
| | `.learnings/` via recommend/inject | |

---

## Evals (Anthropic-style: sensors over vibes)

Prefer **deterministic graders** over self-praise:

```bash
npm run ship:eval     # lint + test + optional build; writes .agents/goals/_eval/last.json
```

Done means **checks pass**, not “looks good.” Add a failing test before bugfixes when practical.

